parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine head gasket failure can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to a loss of power, overheating, and potentially a fire while driving.
Transmission problems can cause sudden loss of power, jerking or slamming into gear, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents.
Loss of motive power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Hybrid battery problems can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
CV axle failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, leading to loss of control and accidents.
Other issues, such as faulty start/stop systems and oil cooler failures, can cause the vehicle to malfunction or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
The failure of the head gasket can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to misfires, overheating, and engine damage, which can result in accidents, strandings, or engine fires.
symptoms: shuddering or hesitation when starting the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Start/Stop system can cause loss of motive power, stalling, and accidents.
